	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=116766><span id= >Karidan</span></a><br><span id=notbold>9 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'm one of those warriors that can never have enough clickies. Its really sad when you get to the point that you can fill all 15 of your buff slots by yourself and still have more clickies that you haven't used yet. Anyway, this is one of those obscure treasures that nobody seems to have ever heard of. Those that will take the time to look it up will probably think nothing more of this than a toy with no practical use. For the most part that's right... being a tree doesn't do much for you anymore... Being a tree used to make you indifferent to almost anything but undead but in many zones it doesn't seem to make much of a differnce anymore. <br>One of the benefits of this item that most people overlook is the self root effect. I like to think of this effect as a 36 minute self root that also makes you look like a tree. What benefit could that possibly have you ask? Consider mobs that fear... when a mob fears you, you are going to run away from it uncontrollably. Spirit of Wolf / Eagle complicates things even more since you will run farther away before the fear wears off. When you are feared its easy to run off and get aggro and possibly even wipe your raid. If you are standing in front of a mob in treeform it can fear you all it likes and you will not move an inch... when fear wears off you just turn back around and continue fighting. I remember back in my younger years when we used to kill Wuoshi they would tell everyone to turn RUN off and click off your sow because of the fear. This item solves that for you, especially if you are doing ranged damgage and having the mob move a bit doesn't affect you much. This same scenario would also apply to mobs that charm... if you are charmed you will not be able to melee attack your group because you are rooted. The nice part about the root effect is that you can click it off whenever you choose and the effect is INSTANT. Now in order for this item to be practial you really need to get two or three of them and keep them recharged. Granted, this item will not work indoors and its application is somewhat limited but some of us like to prepare for anything, just my 2cp.<br>Just found 2 of these for sale on my server, fun fun <br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Dec 24 00:12:18 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
